* Description: Install and run Raspbian on Raspberry Pi 4 Computer * 

In order to understand the basics of what I will be using to complete the goal build, I used Quick Start Guide that come with Raspi 4 computer from vilros.com to install and setup Raspbian on the computer.

Link to the Quick Start Guide: https://cdn.shopify.com/s/files/1/0195/1344/2404/files/QUICKSTART_09_06_2017_EDITION.pdf?4444633349731588961

Problems faced: 

1) The old TV/LCD showed "No Signal" shortly followed by blank screen. 

Problem Solved: 

Step 1: Formatted the SD card. 
Step 2: Added hdmi_force_hotploug=1 (from https://www.raspberrypi.org/forums/viewtopic.php?t=34061)

2) Mouse pointer lagging 

Problem Solved: 

Step 1: Open the terminal
Step 2: Follow the rules described here (https://thepihut.com/blogs/raspberry-pi-tutorials/fix-that-laggy-wifi-mouse#:~:text=If%20you%20find%20your%20WiFi,out%20the%20laggy%20mouse%20movement)

Learnings: 

How to effectively use GNU Nano text editor. 
File System Formats FAT 32 and FAT 16. 
Advantages of using Raspi.
Basic Raspi Setup. 